  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Stilte in de klas,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, focuses on the significance of silence in educational environments. While it has yet to receive citations or community discussions in notable online platforms, its underlying themes resonate with educational practices that intersect with sustainability, as it is associated with one Sustainable Development Goal. Its presence on commercial platforms like Amazon and Goodreads indicates a potential for wider public engagement.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2022, \"Stilte in de klas\" by Leuven University Press explores the multifaceted role of silence within the classroom context. Although it currently has no recorded citations or public discussions on major platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, the book positions itself within the broader discourse of educational policies and practices. Its connection to sustainability is noteworthy, with affiliations to one Sustainable Development Goal, hinting at the potential relevance of its content to ongoing conversations about education's role in promoting sustainable development.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of event data and online mentions, the book is accessible on commercial platforms, which suggests an opportunity for gaining readership outside traditional academic spheres. Its availability on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads could serve as a gateway for fostering public interest in the themes presented. Encouragingly, this commercial linkage underscores a pathway to elevate discussions about educational silence among practitioners and the general public.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of online engagement metrics might reflect the nascent stage of its visibility in academic discussions, which may change as more educators and policymakers engage with the text. As educational environments increasingly emphasize student well-being and reflective practices, works like \"Stilte in de klas\" could become integral to policy discussions, aligning with a greater societal focus on the importance of educational settings.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In conclusion, while \"Stilte in de klas\" has not yet made significant waves in the academic or public discourse, its potential for impact exists, especially in relation to sustainability and educational practices. As the conversation around silence in classrooms becomes more relevant amidst changing pedagogical frameworks, this text may serve as a valuable resource for those looking to explore the intersections of silence, community engagement, and educational policy.</p>",
